      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "The later failure in the ancestor-commits test looks like it may be a second timing assumption in the same functional test, not just the `abortrescan` path fixed by #35512. In both snippets the rescan can complete very quickly before the test observes the intended blocked/aborted state. If possible, making the test hold the rescan at a deterministic synchronization point would avoid asserting on a race between the RPC call and a very short rescan.\n",
